1. Problem Statement

Item| Description
Problem| Businesses often struggle to track inventory manually, leading to stock shortages, overstocking, data inaccuracies, and inefficient operations.
Solution| The Inventory Management System provides a centralized platform to manage products, categories, suppliers, stock movements, and inventory reports in real time.

2. Entities / Data Model

Entity| Fields
User| name, email, password, role, isActive, createdAt
Category| name, description, createdBy
Product| name, description, category, sku, price, quantity, image, createdBy
Supplier| name, email, phone, address, createdBy
Stock In| product, supplier, quantity, date, createdBy
Stock Out| product, quantity, date, createdBy
Inventory Transaction| product, transactionType, quantity, date, user

3. Workflow

Step| Process
1| User logs into the system
2| Admin creates categories
3| Admin adds suppliers
4| Admin adds products
5| Stock is added through Stock In
6| Stock is removed through Stock Out
7| Inventory updates automatically
8| Users view inventory reports and statistics

